Activity 15: OpenStack Installation (Neutron, Horizon, Cinder)

1. Objectives

Create a workflow to install OpenStack using Ansible as your Infrastructure as Code

(IaC).

2. Intended Learning Outcomes

  1. Analyze the advantages and disadvantages of cloud services

  2. Evaluate different Cloud deployment and service models

  3. Create a workflow to install and configure OpenStack base services using Ansible as documentation and execution.

3. Resources

Oracle VirtualBox (Hypervisor) 1x Ubuntu VM or Centos VM

4. Tasks

  1. Create a new repository for this activity.

  2. Create a playbook that converts the steps in the following items in https://docs.openstack.org/install-guide/

    1. Neutron

    2. Horizon

    3. Cinder

    4. Create different plays in installing per server type (controller, compute etc.) and identify it as a group in the Inventory file.

    5. Add, commit and push it to your GitHub repo.

Reflections:

Answer the following:

1. Describe Neutron, Horizon and Cinder services

- In Ubuntu, think of Neutron as the backstage coordinator making sure all the digital devices in a cloud setup can communicate smoothly. Horizon is like the friendly face at the front desk, offering an easy-to-use website where users can manage their cloud stuff without needing to be tech experts. Meanwhile, Cinder acts as the storage organizer, ensuring that all the data is neatly stored and easily accessible for the virtual machines. Essentially, they work together to keep everything running smoothly in the background, making the cloud experience user-friendly and efficient.

Conclusions:

- To conclude achieving the learning outcomes of this hands on activities provides me with the main understanding of the cloud services. this enables me to analize the advantages and disadvantages enables informed in decision making in adapting cloud solutions. The evaluation of the different cloud deployment services empowered us individuals to tailor cloud setups for specific needs. The creaton of workflow on installing aswell as condifuting openstack with ansible not only enhances my technical skills but it also forsters my efficient documentation and execution practices. All in all i can conclude that all the hands on activities that i have took on this Course has equipped me with a holistic perspective and practical skills that are essential for navigating the dynamic landscape of cloud computing. Thank you.
